        <updateDate>2021-04-23T14:22:11Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Pandemic Healthcare Access Act</strong></p> <p>This bill preserves the eligibility of health savings account (HSA) participants covered by any health plan&nbsp;during the coronavirus emergency period. The <em>coronavirus emergency period</em> is the period beginning on March 13, 2020, and ending on the later of (1) the last day on which a presidential declaration of emergency under the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act with respect to the coronavirus (i.e., the virus that causes COVID-19)&nbsp;is in effect, or (2) the last day on which&nbsp;a presidential declaration of national emergency under the National Emergencies Act with respect to the coronavirus&nbsp;is in effect. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
